# Frontend Type Definitions

**MANDATORY**: All TypeScript types and interfaces MUST come from `frontend/src/types/`.

## Rules

- ✅ Import from `@/types/[domain]` (e.g. `import type { Item } from '@/types/item'`)
- ✅ Add new types to `frontend/src/types/` — one file per domain (item.ts, machine.ts, factory.ts, etc.)
- ❌ DO NOT import from root `types.ts` — that file is legacy (Supabase-based) for old pages only

## Examples

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
import type { Item } from '@/types/item';
import type { Machine } from '@/types/machine';
import type { MachineItem } from '@/types/machineItem';
import type { Factory } from '@/types/factory';

// ❌ WRONG (legacy)
import { Machine, Part } from '@/types';
```
